# Bonfire E2E release-gate box — operator environment
#
# This file is OPTIONAL. The host driver (tests/e2e/scripts/e2e-box.sh)
# auto-detects the operator's auth mode at startup:
#
#   1. Claude Max OAuth (preferred when available) — if you have Claude Code
#      logged in (~/.claude/.credentials.json exists), the driver bind-mounts
#      your credentials into the container. No .env staging required. Cost is
#      counted against your Claude Max plan, not your Anthropic console
#      billing.
#
#   2. Anthropic console API key — if you do not have Claude Max, copy this
#      file to .env, paste an active key on the line below, and re-run. Cost
#      lands on your Anthropic console billing (~$0.10–$1 per fire); set a
#      daily-spend cap.
#
# .env is gitignored.
#
# IMPORTANT: this file ships with ALL lines commented out. To opt into the
# API-key path, copy this file to .env, uncomment the line below, and replace
# the REPLACE_ME placeholder with a real sk-ant-… key. If you leave the line
# commented, the driver auto-detects Claude Max OAuth instead — the .env is
# treated as if absent.
#
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-api03-REPLACE_ME
# Optional model pin
# ANTHROPIC_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-7-20260101
